 "segments": [
  {
   "start": 0.0,
   "end": 4.34,
   "text": "In China, the man at the shop, the bus driver, your neighbor, they're all your uncle or"
  },
  {
   "start": 4.34,
   "end": 4.92,
   "text": "auntie."
  },
  {
   "start": 5.22,
   "end": 8.62,
   "text": "But here's the irony, there's no single Chinese word for uncle at all."
  },
  {
   "start": 9.0,
   "end": 10.92,
   "text": "There are, at least eight, let me explain."
  },
  {
   "start": 11.6,
   "end": 12.98,
   "text": "English has one lazy word."
  },
  {
   "start": 13.96,
   "end": 15.88,
   "text": "Uncle for a whole crowd of different people."
  },
  {
   "start": 16.6,
   "end": 19.76,
   "text": "Chinese refuses to be that vague, it needs to know exactly who you mean."
  },
  {
   "start": 20.24,
   "end": 22.12,
   "text": "Is he your father's brother or your mother's?"
  },
  {
   "start": 22.36,
   "end": 23.92,
   "text": "Is he older than your parent or younger?"
  },
  {
   "start": 24.26,
   "end": 25.66,
   "text": "Is he blood or married in?"
  },
  {
   "start": 26.08,
   "end": 27.78,
   "text": "Every combination is a different word."
  },
  {
   "start": 28.6,
   "end": 32.44,
   "text": "Father's older brother, father's younger brother, mother's brother, the husband of your father's"
  },
  {
   "start": 32.44,
   "end": 33.72,
   "text": "sister, you get the idea."
  },
  {
   "start": 34.3,
   "end": 36.38,
   "text": "There's no neutral uncle to fall back on."
  },
  {
   "start": 36.78,
   "end": 42.08,
   "text": "The word itself tells you the exact relationship, and yet, Chinese uses these very same family"
  },
  {
   "start": 42.08,
   "end": 43.32,
   "text": "words for total strangers."
  },
  {
   "start": 43.86,
   "end": 49.08,
   "text": "You call an older man uncle, an older woman auntie, a young woman big sister, as a sign"
  },
  {
   "start": 49.08,
   "end": 50.02,
   "text": "of warmth and respect."
  },
  {
   "start": 50.42,
   "end": 55.18,
   "text": "Everyone gets slotted into the family, a language incredibly precise about family, that"
  },
  {
